Thank you. I know I start every meeting this way, but it's just my favorite part of the meeting. So this evening, we have the privilege of having Medford High School's Science Fair awardees here with us. And so I'm going to have Director of Science, Mr. Rocco Sieri, do just a little bit of framing for us before he welcomes the students up to talk about their project and teach all of us a little bit more about science this evening.

7
00:02:46,840 --> 00:03:14,110
Good evening, Madam Mayor and school committee members. This is probably one of the most exciting meetings to be at in terms of what the students bring to the Medford Public Schools. Their creativity and ingenuity in class is often not seen on the day-to-day, but at the end of each year, we've been doing an annual science fair for really

8
00:03:14,110 --> 00:03:32,774
more years than can be imagined, and they've been continuous in Medford since, oh, probably the 1960s or so. This year, I'm excited to be able to bring a few people forward, to introduce them and let them speak about their projects.

9
